# Regression: a `(...)` statement after an enum declaration must NOT be parsed
# as a payload list for the preceding nullary member. A payload `(` is a payload
# only when attached to the member name (`failed(int str)`); a detached paren
# (whitespace or newline before it) belongs to the following code, and the
# member is nullary. Before the fix, the quotation below was swallowed by the
# enum declaration.
enum C = red | green | blue

(green) x str wl
[1 2 3] (0 >) filter len str wl
